From 0deb4630949bfda3c7db5047df27ce343aafe00c Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Donatas Abraitis <donatas@opensourcerouting.org>
Date: Mon, 2 Mar 2026 11:34:34 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] bgpd: Fix condition when evaluating paths

Original commit said:

Let's broaden this scope a tiny bit to allow for matches where the number of
nexthops is 1 and the nexthop->ifindex is the same as the interfaces ifindex
for the up/down event.

But the condition was incorrect according to the definition.

That leads to routes being flushed incorrectly.

When nexthop_num > 1, the first clause is false, so the whole continue is
skipped, and the DOWN processing runs BGP_NEXTHOP_VALID is unset, nexthop_num
is set to 0, evaluate_paths() is called, which means paths are withdrawn...

Fixes: d1252ec ("bgpd: On interface up/down events allow for more interfaces to be affected")

Upstream-Status: Backport [https://github.com/FRRouting/frr/commit/0deb4630949bfda3c7db5047df27ce343aafe00c]

Signed-off-by: Donatas Abraitis <donatas@opensourcerouting.org>
(cherry picked from commit 5de395fc8ac476cb17bbc911f527ead60e841fb4)
Signed-off-by: Jonas Gorski <jonas.gorski@bisdn.de>
---
 bgpd/bgp_nht.c | 4 ++--
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/bgpd/bgp_nht.c b/bgpd/bgp_nht.c
index e78d9fe2059d..32d50e6cc58e 100644
--- a/bgpd/bgp_nht.c
+++ b/bgpd/bgp_nht.c
@@ -802,8 +802,8 @@ static void bgp_nht_ifp_table_handle(struct bgp *bgp,
 	}
 
 	frr_each (bgp_nexthop_cache, table, bnc) {
-		if ((bnc->nexthop_num == 1 && bnc->nexthop &&
-		     bnc->nexthop->ifindex != ifp->ifindex) &&
+		if (!(bnc->nexthop_num == 1 && bnc->nexthop &&
+		      bnc->nexthop->ifindex == ifp->ifindex) &&
 		    (bnc->ifindex_ipv6_ll != ifp->ifindex))
 			continue;
 
-- 
